      "name": "Social Phobia Inventory",
      "description": "The Social Phobia Inventory was derived by Duke University\u0027s Behavioural Science Department. It is used to measure and screen for the extent of social phobia and anxiety disorder through 17 questions that require self-assessment around the three important aspects of fear, avoidance and psychological discomfort."
